    "description": "&quot;Society in every state is a blessing, but government even in its best state is but a necessary evil.&quot;\n– Thomas Paine, &quot;Common Sense&quot; (1776).\n\n&quot;The process of writing [&amp; drawing ?] has something infinite about it. Even though it is interrupted each night, it is one single notation.&quot;\n– Elias Canetti\n\n&quot;I personally think intellectual property is an oxymoron. Physical objects have a completely different natural economy than intellectual goods. It's a tricky thing to try to own something that remains in your possession even after you give it to many others.&quot;\n– John Perry Barlow",
